\pard\qc\b 1. INTRODUCTION\b0\par
\pard\ql\b i) Introduction of the system\b0\par
\pard\ql\b a) Project Title:\b0 ChatBhar Web \u8212? High-Performance Social CMS + Channels + Messaging\par
\pard\ql\b b) Category:\b0 Web-based Social Media and Communication System\par
\pard\ql\b Overview:\b0 ChatBhar is a browser-based application combining social content publishing and messaging in one platform. The system supports authentication, profile setup, content posting, creator/channel management, and direct/group chat with media support.\par
\pard\ql\b ii) Background\b0\par
\pard\ql\b a) Introduction of the Company:\b0 No formal company details are defined in the repository; the project is documented as a product prototype/academic implementation.\par
\pard\ql\b b) Brief note on existing system (if applicable):\b0 Existing social platforms often separate publishing and chat modules; ChatBhar unifies both workflows and includes local fallback execution when backend services are unavailable.\par
\pard\ql\b iii) Objectives of the system\b0\par
\pard\ql\pntext\f0 1.\tab{\*\pn\pnlvlbody\pnf0\pnstart1\pndec{\pnsep\pnsp}}Provide one integrated social + messaging experience.\par
\pard\ql\pntext\f0 2.\tab{\*\pn\pnlvlbody\pnf0\pnstart1\pndec{\pnsep\pnsp}}Support rich media posting (shorts, carousel, long video, stories).\par
\pard\ql\pntext\f0 3.\tab{\*\pn\pnlvlbody\pnf0\pnstart1\pndec{\pnsep\pnsp}}Enable secure signup/login with username lifecycle controls.\par
\pard\ql\pntext\f0 4.\tab{\*\pn\pnlvlbody\pnf0\pnstart1\pndec{\pnsep\pnsp}}Offer responsive feed interaction and chat communication.\par
\pard\ql\pntext\f0 5.\tab{\*\pn\pnlvlbody\pnf0\pnstart1\pndec{\pnsep\pnsp}}Maintain usability in static mode using browser storage.\par
\pard\ql\b iv) Scope of the system\b0\par
\pard\ql Scope includes account onboarding, profile editing, content upload and management, feed engagement, user discovery, relationships/follow requests, and messaging (direct and group).\par
\pard\ql\b v) System Architecture\b0\par
\pard\ql\pntext\f0 -\tab{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf0\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}Frontend: HTML/CSS/JavaScript SPA\par
\pard\ql\pntext\f0 -\tab{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf0\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}Optional cloud services: Firebase Auth/Firestore/Storage\par
\pard\ql\pntext\f0 -\tab{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf0\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}Fallback mode: localStorage-powered API abstraction\par
\pard\ql\pntext\f0 -\tab{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf0\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}Persistent data files: db/auth-db.json + uploads folder\par
\pard\ql\b vi) End users\b0\par
\pard\ql General social users, content creators/channel operators, and messaging users (one-to-one and group chat).\par
\pard\ql\b vii) Software/Hardware used\b0\par
\pard\ql\pntext\f0 -\tab{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf0\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}Software: Node.js, npm, browser runtime, Firebase SDK, Playwright test tooling\par
\pard\ql\pntext\f0 -\tab{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf0\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}Hardware: Standard desktop/laptop with internet for cloud mode\par
\page
\pard\qc\b 2. SRS\b0\par
\pard\ql\b i) Introduction (Brief write-up about SRS)\b0\par
\pard\ql This Software Requirements Specification defines expected behavior, constraints, interfaces, and quality attributes of ChatBhar Web across full backend mode and local fallback mode.\par
\pard\ql\b ii) Overall Description\b0\par
\pard\ql The application is a tab-driven single page app with five primary modules: Home, Explore, Post, Channels, and Chat. User data, posts, and message data are rendered dynamically and synchronized either through Firebase/backend APIs or through local browser persistence.\par
\pard\ql\b iii) Special Requirements (if any)\b0\par
\pard\ql\pntext\f0 -\tab{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf0\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}Gmail-only signup policy (as project rule)\par
\pard\ql\pntext\f0 -\tab{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf0\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}Username uniqueness checks and change-policy limits\par
\pard\ql\pntext\f0 -\tab{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf0\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}Media format handling for stories/shorts/LTV/carousel\par
\pard\ql\pntext\f0 -\tab{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf0\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}Graceful API fallback behavior without crashing UX\par
\pard\ql\b iv) Functional Requirements\b0\par
\pard\ql\b a) Module 1: Authentication and User Management\b0\par
\pard\ql - Signup/login, session persistence, username onboarding, profile update.\par
\pard\ql\b b) Module 2: Content Upload and Publishing\b0\par
\pard\ql - Type selection, drag/drop or file picker, caption/description validation, progress handling, publish flow.\par
\pard\ql\b c) Module 3: Feed and Explore\b0\par
\pard\ql - Feed rendering, user search, active profile discovery, public interaction support (like/comment/share).\par
\pard\ql\b d) Module 4: Channel Management\b0\par
\pard\ql - Creator posts listing, metadata editing, creative suite re-entry, post deletion.\par
\pard\ql\b e) Module 5: Messaging\b0\par
\pard\ql - DM/group chat, media preview, typing/presence signaling (mode-dependent), reaction and reply-capable interactions.\par
\pard\ql\b f) Module 6: Data Services\b0\par
\pard\ql - API request handling, local fallback handlers, data serialization and restore.\par
\page
\pard\qc\b 3. SYSTEM DESIGN\b0\par
\pard\ql\b Introduction\b0\par
\pard\ql ChatBhar follows an event-driven client architecture where UI components are mounted in a single HTML shell and application state is managed via JavaScript variables + persisted stores.\par
\pard\ql\b Description of Functions\b0\par
\pard\ql\pntext\f0 -\tab{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf0\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}Initialization: hydrate state, bind events, start sync listeners\par
\pard\ql\pntext\f0 -\tab{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf0\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}Rendering: home feed, channels, explore list, chat messages\par
\pard\ql\pntext\f0 -\tab{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf0\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}Mutation: create/update/delete posts; send messages; follow/request actions\par
\pard\ql\b Data Flow Design\b0\par
\pard\ql User Action \u8594? Validation \u8594? API/Fallback Handler \u8594? Persisted State \u8594? UI Re-render.\par
\pard\ql\b Modular decomposition of the system\b0\par
\pard\ql 1) Auth Module\par
2) Profile Module\par
3) Upload/Creative Module\par
4) Feed/Viewer Module\par
5) Explore/Relationship Module\par
6) Chat/Conversation Module\par
7) Storage + API Utility Layer\par
\page
\pard\qc\b 4. PROGRAM CODE LISTING\b0\par
\pard\ql\b Code with Title\b0\par
\pard\ql\pntext\f0 -\tab{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf0\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}index.html \u8212? Layout, tab screens, form shells, modal containers\par
\pard\ql\pntext\f0 -\tab{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf0\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}styles.css \u8212? Theming, responsive structure, component styling\par
\pard\ql\pntext\f0 -\tab{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf0\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}app.js \u8212? Core business logic + fallback API + realtime hooks\par
\pard\ql\pntext\f0 -\tab{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf0\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}db/auth-db.json \u8212? NoSQL-like persisted user schema\par
\pard\ql\pntext\f0 -\tab{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf0\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}verify_*.spec.cjs / verify_*.py \u8212? Automated UI verification scripts\par
\page
